<paragraph blockId="5.[151,657,1655,1682]" box="[151,657,1655,1682]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,657,1655,1682]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,657,1655,1682]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[207,453,1655,1681]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Lyonsifusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ansatus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,453,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Lyonsifusus ansatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1726,2003]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="245" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
In species complexes within several Fusinine genera, the morphologies of typical specimens diverge into several or many diverse forms. Given the present depauperate understanding of the biology of individual fusinine taxa, taxonomists have tended to regard these complexes simply as variable species. Examples include 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="colus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1436,1798,1823]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Fusinus colus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[158,337,1834,1859]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" refId="ref27750" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Caroli Linnaei ... Systema Naturae per Regna tria Naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis ... Editio decima reformata. Tom. 1. Animalia. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae [Stockholm], iv + 823 pp." type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
of the western Pacific, 
<taxonomicName authority="(A. Adams, 1864)" authorityName="A. Adams" authorityYear="1864" baseAuthorityName="A. Adams" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[627,987,1834,1859]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Fusinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis box="[627,642,1836,1859]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">F</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[659,768,1834,1859]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">perplexus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Adams, A." box="[787,979,1834,1859]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" pagination="105 - 108" refId="ref23897" refString="Adams, A. (1864) On the species of Fusidae which inhabit the seas of Japan. Journal of the Proceedings of the Linnean Society, Zoology, 7, 105 - 108. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1863. tb 02106. x" type="journal article" year="1864">A. Adams, 1864</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
of Japanese seas, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lamarck, 1816)" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1816" baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1816" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Africofusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ocellifer">
<emphasis box="[1204,1435,1834,1859]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Africofusus ocellifer</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck, J. B. P. A. de" box="[158,334,1870,1895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" pagination="391 - 488" refId="ref27408" refString="Lamarck, J. B. P. A. de M. (1816) Tableau Encyclopedique et Methodique des Trois Regnes de la Nature. Vingt-Troisieme Partie. Mollusques et Polypes Divers. Liste des Objets Representes dans les Planches se Cette Livraison. Mme. Veuve Agasse, Imprimeur-Libraire, Paris, 16 pp., pls. 391 - 488, 431 bis, 431 bis *." type="book chapter" year="1816">Lamarck, 1816</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[388,536,1870,1895]" name="South Africa" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Roding, 1798)" authorityName="Roding" authorityYear="1798" baseAuthorityName="Roding" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[597,1090,1870,1895]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Marmorofusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nicobaricus">
<emphasis box="[597,904,1870,1895]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Marmorofusus nicobaricus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Roding, P. F." box="[923,1081,1870,1895]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" refId="ref30526" refString="Roding, P. F. (1798) Museum Boltenianum sive catalogus cimeliorum e tribus regnis naturae ... Pars Secunda continens Conchylia sive Testacea univalvia, bivalvia &amp; multivalvia. Typis Johan. Christi, Trappii, Hamburg, 199 pp." type="book" year="1798">Röding, 1798</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
of the Indo-west Pacific (see Snyder &amp; Lyons 2014). Two examples in the western Atlantic include the group of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Philippi, 1850)" authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1850" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1850" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Goniofusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="strigatus">
<emphasis box="[1090,1323,1907,1931]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Goniofusus strigatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Philippi, R. A." pageId="5" pageNumber="244" pagination="89 - 138" refId="ref29752" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1850 [1847 - 1851]) Abbildungen und Beschreibungen neuer oder wenig gekannter Conchylien. Band III (Dritter Band; cover date 1851). Theodor Fischer, Cassell, 82 + 138 pp., pls. [pp. 1 - 50 (1847) + 51 - 82 (1848) + 1 - 88 (1849) + 89 - 138 (1850 ))" type="book chapter" year="1850">Philippi, 1850</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName authority="(Grabau, 1904)" authorityName="Grabau" authorityYear="1904" baseAuthorityName="Grabau" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[244,595,1942,1967]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Goniofusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis box="[244,261,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[279,408,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">brasiliensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Grabau, A. W." box="[428,587,1942,1967]" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" pagination="1 - 193" refId="ref26227" refString="Grabau, A. W. (1904) Phylogeny of Fusus and its allies. Smithsonian Miscellaneous Collections, 44 (1417), i-iii + 1 - 193." type="journal article" year="1904">Grabau, 1904</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
of central and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[888,956,1942,1967]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[1065,1293,1943,1967]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Lyonsifusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ansatus">
<emphasis box="[1065,1293,1943,1967]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Lyonsifusus ansatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex of northern South America and the Lesser Antilles. The latter group contains several named taxa, of which we classify all except one as the variable 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gmelin, 1791)" authorityName="Gmelin" authorityYear="1791" baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[492,792,151,176]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Lyonsifusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="245" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ansatus">
<emphasis box="[492,610,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="245">L. ansatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gmelin, J. F." box="[625,784,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="245" pagination="3021 - 4120" refId="ref26153" refString="Gmelin, J. F. (1791) C Caroli a Linne. Systema naturae per regna tria naturae: secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. 13 th Edition. Tome 1. Pars 6. Vermes, Testacea. impensis Georg. Emanuel. Beer, Lipsiae, pp. 1100 pp. [pp. 3021 - 4120]" type="book chapter" year="1791">Gmelin, 1791</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(see below). The exception is 
<taxonomicName authority="(Macsotay &amp; Campos Villarroel, 2001)" authorityName="Macsotay &amp; Campos Villarroel" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Macsotay &amp; Campos Villarroel" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Lyonsifusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="245" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carvalhoriosi">
<emphasis box="[1145,1436,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="245">Lyonsifusus carvalhoriosi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Macsotay, O. &amp; Campos Villarroel, R." box="[158,616,188,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="245" refId="ref28155" refString="Macsotay, O. &amp; Campos Villarroel, R. (2001) Moluscos representatives de la Platforma de Margarita, Venezuela. Editora Rivolta, Valencia, 280 pp." type="book" year="2001">Macsotay &amp; Campos Villarroel, 2001</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which clearly is related to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1791" box="[1028,1151,189,212]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Lyonsifusus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="245" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ansatus">
<emphasis box="[1028,1151,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="245">L. ansatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group but whose shell morphology is sufficiently distinctive to merit recognition as a separate species.
</paragraph>
